				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">All very good points! Back when they started advertising the sizes of NES and Master System games, hardly any games reached the 1 megabyte mark (the Master System only got there because of brazilian exclusives, and the NES never did), and fractional numbers probably wouldn't sound as impressive. Plus, &quot;megabits&quot; was the standard way to measure the size of memory chips back then, so it simply made sense to use that to describe cartridges that used such chips.</div>

