				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Megabits is not only for marketting (although I agree it definitely played a major role), but is also the standard size when buying RAM or ROM components. Because it's the only unit that can represent size regardless of data bus size. Counting bytes is fine, but it assumes 8-bit words, which is not always the case.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

